Nothing else going on here, no nice lobby, no pool, only adult type restaurant named "Whisky" like I would take my kids there!	"Luxury Boutique," "Personalized Service" and "Spectacular Setting" are not just words in the hotel's promotional materials, they are a "Lifestyle" at The Sutton Place.	We checked in and met the most pleasant and helpful woman ever, Michelle G.. She overheard my husband telling the bell hop that it was his birthday so she offered a room upgrade for a very small charge.	It has not been changed since the building was built 20+ years ago, the bathroom tiles are chipped with dirty grout, and there are NOT flat screen TVs in every room as their website advertises.